  "summary": {
    "as": "Public Law",
    "asOf": "2022-10-10",
    "date": "2022-12-21T14:40:17Z",
    "text": "Small Project Efficient and Effective Disaster Recovery Act or the SPEED Recovery Act\n\nThis act increases to $1 million the threshold for eligibility for assistance for what qualifies as a small project under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act, thereby allowing more recovery projects to proceed under simplified procedures.\n\nThe threshold must be reviewed every three years.\n\nThe Inspector General of the Department of Homeland Security must conduct an audit, and report to Congress, on whether there has been waste and abuse as a result of the change in the threshold."
  },
